948.025(1)(d) - Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child

Shall not have contact with S.M. (d/o/b 05/14/2004), witness - M.R. (d/o/b 07/29/1982) or any of her children, their residences; schools: Madison & Janet Berry; nor McDonalds in Menasha.  No contact means no contact in person, in writing, by phone, computer, through a third person or otherwise, except through the defendant's attorney.
The defendant must have installed a Global Positioning System, with exclusion zone-not to be within 5 miles of residences, schools or places of employment for victim/witnesses,  before release and shall not tamper with or remove the system without court approval.
Shall comply with all rules established by the vendor.
Shall not remove or otherwise tamper with the Global Positioning System.  The Global Positioning System may only be removed by the vendor.
Surrender Passport to Clerk of Court Office within 48 hours of release from jail, excluding weekends or holidays.
Shall not leave state of Wisconsin without permission of the Court. 
Supervised contact is allowed with Angel if a court order exists allowing joint custody, and after child's mother provides list of third party candidates for supervisors.
Shall not have contact with any juveniles without a parent present.
Defendant may have one visit with officer to retrieve just basic belongings to get by while case is pending.  Time to be set up through Victim/Witness coordinators in the District Attorney's Office.
